1. Introduction¶

Context¶

Since 2008, guests and hosts have used Airbnb to travel in a more unique, personalized way. As part of the Airbnb Inside initiative, this dataset describes the listing activity of homestays in Seattle, WA.

Content¶

The following Airbnb activity is included in this Seattle dataset: Listings, including full descriptions and average review score Reviews, including unique id for each reviewer and detailed comments * Calendar, including listing id and the price and availability for that day

Inspiration¶

  • Can you describe the vibe of each Seattle neighborhood using listing descriptions?
  • What are the busiest times of the year to visit Seattle? By how much do prices spike?
  • Is there a general upward trend of both new Airbnb listings and total Airbnb visitors to Seattle?

For more ideas, visualizations of all Seattle datasets can be found here.

Acknowledgement¶

This dataset is part of Airbnb Inside, and the original source can be found here
.

df_listings = pd.read_csv('../input/listings.csv')
print(len(df_listings))

dolar = ['price','weekly_price','monthly_price','security_deposit','cleaning_fee','extra_people']
for p in dolar:
    df_listings[p] = df_listings[p].str.replace('$','')
    df_listings[p] = df_listings[p].str.replace(',','')
    df_listings[p] = df_listings[p].astype(float)
    
df_listings['host_response_rate'] = df_listings['host_response_rate'].str.replace('%','')
df_listings['host_response_rate'] = df_listings['host_response_rate'].astype(float)
df_listings[p] = df_listings[p].astype(float)

df_listings['city'] = df_listings['city'].str.split()
df_listings['city'] = df_listings['city'].apply(lambda x:  ' '.join(x))

df_listings["host_verifications"] = df_listings['host_verifications'].str.replace('[,]',' ')
df_listings['host_verifications'] = df_listings["host_verifications"].str.split()
df_listings['cn_host_verifications'] = df_listings["host_verifications"].apply(lambda x: len(x))

df_listings["amenities"] = df_listings['amenities'].str.replace('[{,}]',' ')
df_listings['amenities'] = df_listings["amenities"].str.split()
df_listings['cn_amenities'] = df_listings["amenities"].apply(lambda x: len(x))
    
df_listings = df_listings[df_listings['city']=='Seattle']
print(len(df_listings))

url_feature = ['listing_url','thumbnail_url','medium_url','picture_url','xl_picture_url','host_url',
               'host_thumbnail_url','host_picture_url']

for feature1 in url_feature:
    df_listings = df_listings.drop(feature1, axis=1)
    

one_value_feature = ['scrape_id','last_scraped','state','market','country_code','country','has_availability',
                    'calendar_last_scraped','requires_license','jurisdiction_names','host_acceptance_rate']

for feature2 in one_value_feature:
    df_listings = df_listings.drop(feature2, axis=1)
    
all_null_value = ['experiences_offered','license','square_feet']

for feature3 in all_null_value:
    df_listings = df_listings.drop(feature3, axis=1)
    
unused_feature = ['host_id','host_name','host_since','host_location','street','neighbourhood',
                  'neighbourhood_cleansed','zipcode','name','host_neighbourhood','smart_location',
                 'last_review','first_review','calendar_updated','city','host_verifications','amenities',
                 'neighbourhood_group_cleansed']

for feature4 in unused_feature:
    df_listings = df_listings.drop(feature4, axis=1)

Fillna bedrooms - similarity pattern with property_type, bed_type, and bathrooms

In [13]:
index_NaN_bedrooms = list(df["bedrooms"][df["bedrooms"].isnull()].index)
for i in index_NaN_bedrooms :
    bedrooms_med = df["bedrooms"].median()
    bedrooms_pred = df["bedrooms"][((df['property_type'] == df.iloc[i]["property_type"]) & (df['bed_type'] == df.iloc[i]["bed_type"]) & (df['bathrooms'] == df.iloc[i]["bathrooms"]))].median()
    if not np.isnan(bedrooms_pred) :
        df['bedrooms'].iloc[i] = bedrooms_pred
    else :
        df['bedrooms'].iloc[i] = bedrooms_med
